### Description

I have a stylesheet for mapping font icons which looks like:
```scss
:root {
  --icon-menu: "\e600";
  --icon-calendar: "\e601";
}
```
When serving locally with `optimzation.styles.minify = false` the resulting css looks something like (just like i expected):
```css
:root {
  --icon-menu: "ÓòÄ";
  --icon-calendar: "ÓòÅ";
}
```
However if i turn on the style minify optimization (in the prod build or with any other config) the unicode characters will be escaped as documented here https://esbuild.github.io/api/#charset by esbuild when running minify without the charset=utf8

Now I am asking whether this could be a bug in https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/blob/847083698d217a4949d68642fb153d17be8e8e9d/packages/angular_devkit/build_angular/src/tools/webpack/plugins/css-optimizer-plugin.ts#L148 where I think this minification process is called or is there another side to that story?

### Minimal Reproduction

create a scss file like:
```scss
:root {
  --icon-menu: "\e600";
  --icon-calendar: "\e601";
}
```
set `optimzation.styles.minify = true`
run `ng build`
look at the generated output stylesheet -> the unicode characters are escaped but should not

